ey are also routed into the same mismatched-divisor logic that can later produce an underfunding/last-claim failure.\n\nExploitation / reproduction notes (PoC highlights)\n1) Late-join rounding deficit leading to final-claim failure (SBT_DECIMALS = 6):\n- Ensure the category has passed its cliff and is actively vesting (cliff_months_remaining == 0, vesting_months_remaining > 0), and in non-local-testing ensure full_months_since_last_claim == 0 so adding is allowed.\n- Add an investor with category_add_investor / add_investor_to_category using an amount that creates unfavorable rounding, e.g.:\n  a) Example A (19\u219218 months):\n     - Suppose 19 vesting months remaining.\n     - Allocate 100 SBT (100,000,000 base units) such that (amount % 18) < (amount % 19).\n     - Onboarding sets investor.cliff_months_remaining = 1 and reduces vesting_months_remaining to 18.\n     - Category reservation increment uses 100,000,000 / 19 = 5,263,157; over 19 months this is 99,999,983.\n     - Investor monthly allocation is 100,000,000 / 18 = 5,555,555; over 18 months investor expects 99,999,990.\n     - After 17 successful claims, the 18th claim attempts 5,555,555 but only 5,555,548 remains allocated (deficit 7 base units), causing the claim to fail (insufficient balance / underflow revert depending on the path), effectively locking the final month (~5.5% of total allocation in that example narrative).\n  b) Example B (24\u219223 months):\n     - Start with category.vesting_months_remaining == 24 and cliff_months_remaining == 0.\n     - Allocate 100 SBT (100,000,000 base units).\n     - Onboarding reduces investor.vesting_months_remaining from 24 to 23 and sets investor.cliff_months_remaining = 1.\n     - Category total_allocated_tokens_monthly increases by 100,000,000 / 24 = 4,166,666 (summing to 99,999,984 over 24 months).\n     - Investor monthly allocation is 100,000,000 / 23 = 4,347,826 (summing to 99,999,998 over 23 months).\n     - After 22 claims (95,652,172), the final c